## **âœ… 1\. What is Standard Deviation?**

**Standard Deviation (SD)** is the **square root of the variance**.  
 It measures the **average distance of each data point from the mean** in **original units**.

![][image1]

---

### **ğŸ¯ Purpose / Why Use It**

* Tells how much values **"typically deviate"** from the mean

* Brings dispersion back to **original unit** (unlike variance which is squared)

* Essential in **normal distribution**, **confidence intervals**, **error analysis**, **finance**, etc.

---

## **ğŸ”¢ 2\. How to Calculate S.D. (Step-by-Step)**

---

### **ğŸ”¹ A. Raw (Ungrouped) Data**

**Steps:**

1. Find the **mean**

2. Subtract each value from the mean â†’ deviation

3. Square the deviations

4. Add all squares â†’ get variance

5. **Take square root** â†’ get SD
